rComments: Classes are kind of boring, and the slides are typically what's in the book. The prof is very nice though. His midterms are much easier than the final, and assignments are graded pretty loosely.
He is a good professor but his lectures are very, very dry! Overall, he is a great guy and a prof...I'd recommend it :)

Brutally difficult class, but he is able to teach it. He sometimes gets flustered if you don't do the readings and waste time with stupid questions. He is very interesting to talk with in office hours.

Yes, his accents didn't bother me either. Overall a great professor.His slides are clear and as long as you read them carefully and understand them, you will have no problem on the tests.On the other hand,the course is extremely useful and fun.I totally enjoyed the class.

He's a nice professor, like the other rater, his accent doesn't bother me. The tests can be hard so you have to study for them, some of the questions are pretty much a hit or a miss, but if the average is to low he will adjust it. Overall I enjoyed the class
Very nice prof. Clear slides and lectures. His accent does not bother me at all.

Disaster!!! He knows what he teaches, but often it's hard to follow his ideas in class, strong Chinese accent makes it even harder. Very boring prof. Giving VERY hard midterms and exam. Class slides are Ok and it's very important to read the assigned articles to fully understand those slides. Book is barely used.
